Feature: ConfigObject
    In order to manage configurations
    as a Developer
    I need to load and write them

    Scenario Outline: Load a config object
        Given an alias "<alias>"
        And it is loaded
        Then it should return php array

        Scenarios:
            | alias                           |
            | loader.configplusplus.yaml      |
            | loader.configplusplus.xml       |
            | loader.configplusplus.php       |
            | writer.configplusplus.yaml      |
            | writer.configplusplus.xml       |
            | writer.configplusplus.php       |
            | config.configplusplus.test.yaml |
            | config.configplusplus.test.xml  |
            | config.configplusplus.test.php  |

    Scenario Outline: Write a config object
        Given an alias "<alias>"
        And a config node "<node>" with a value "<value>"
        And it is writen to config
        Then it should return true

        Scenarios:
            | alias                           | node | value |
            | loader.configplusplus.yaml      | | |
            | loader.configplusplus.xml       | | |
            | loader.configplusplus.php       | | |
            | writer.configplusplus.yaml      | | |
            | writer.configplusplus.xml       | | |
            | writer.configplusplus.php       | | |
            | config.configplusplus.test.yaml | | |
            | config.configplusplus.test.xml  | | |
            | config.configplusplus.test.php  | | |
